<doc id="531674" wikidata="Q3858380" url="?curid=531674" title="Italian wedding soup">
<text>Italian wedding soup, known in Italian as , is a soup consisting mainly of green vegetables and meat in chicken broth. It is popular in the United States, where it is a staple in many Italian restaurants and diners.

==Origin==
The term &quot;wedding soup&quot; comes from a mistranslation of the Italian language phrase (&#x27;married soup&#x27;). more directly translates to &#x27;wedded broths&#x27;. The marriage of its meats and vegetables inside of its broth is the only matrimony relevant in this context.

